3
00:01:51,370 --> 00:01:53,540
亲爱的孩子们...
My dear children...

4
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:59,000
我迁居纽约已有多年
it is now better than several years since I moved to New York

5
00:01:59,010 --> 00:02:02,750
但不能如愿常见你们
and I haven't seen you as much as I would like to.

6
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:07,330
但愿你们前来观礼
I hope you will come to this ceremony of papal honors

7
00:02:07,340 --> 00:02:09,730
教皇圣谕褒奖我行善
given for my charitable work

8
00:02:09,740 --> 00:02:12,000
纽约 1979年

9
00:02:12,010 --> 00:02:15,470
世上唯有子女是财宝
The only wealth in this world is children.

10
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:18,810
人间财权难以比拟
More than all the money, power on earth

11
00:02:19,380 --> 00:02:21,810
你们是我的至宝
you are my treasure.

12
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:25,810
安东尼 玛莉
Anthony and Mary

13
00:02:25,820 --> 00:02:30,820
为了你们能更好地成长
although I entrusted your education to your mother for your own best interests

14
00:02:30,860 --> 00:02:33,450
我将你们托付给你们的母亲
you know how I look forward to seeing you

15
00:02:33,460 --> 00:02:37,890
我无时无刻都想和你们重聚天伦
and to a new period of harmony in our lives.

16
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:43,260
也许你们能说动母亲来观礼
Perhaps you might prevail upon your mother to come to this celebration

17
00:02:43,270 --> 00:02:49,500
并且时常参加家庭聚会
and that from time to time we can all see each other at family functions.

18
00:02:49,510 --> 00:02:55,750
我爱你们如昔 父字
Anyway, I remain, your loving father.

19
00:03:23,820 --> 00:03:26,550
万福玛利亚 满被圣宠者
Hail Mary, full of grace

20
00:03:29,890 --> 00:03:32,090
女中尔为赞美
blessed art Thou amongst women

21
00:03:33,290 --> 00:03:36,220
尔胎子耶稣并为赞美
and blessed is the fruit of Thy womb,Jesus.

22
00:03:37,630 --> 00:03:40,360
天主圣母玛利亚
Holy Mary, mother of God

23
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:42,520
为我等罪人祈祷
pray for us sinners

24
00:04:06,420 --> 00:04:12,620
全能天主降福这圣萨巴辛徽章
Almighty God, bless the insignia of Saint Sebastian the Martyr

25
00:04:12,630 --> 00:04:19,340
愿徽章之神圣圣化受封人
that it may contribute to the sacredness of him to whom it is given.

26
00:04:31,580 --> 00:04:35,410
麦克 你是否
Do you, Michael

27
00:04:35,420 --> 00:04:38,510
发誓忠于徽章崇高的宗旨
promise to be faithful to the noble purposes of this order

28
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:43,780
赈济贫穷 扶救疾苦
to have a special care for the poor, the needy and those who are ill?

29
00:04:43,790 --> 00:04:45,530
我承诺!
I do so promise.

30
00:05:00,950 --> 00:05:10,950
愿全能者天主圣父 圣子 圣神降福于你
May the blessing of Almighty God Father, Son, and Holy Spirit

31
00:05:10,960 --> 00:05:14,720
与你同在以迨永远
descend upon you and remain with you forever.

32
00:05:14,730 --> 00:05:16,150
阿们!
Amen.

33
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:50,950
文森 名单上没有我们
Vincent, our name's not on the list.

34
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:55,220
那就写上去
Write it in.

35
00:06:55,230 --> 00:06:57,650
曼西尼 M-A-N-I-N-I
Mancini. M-A-N-C-l-N-I.

36
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:00,390
有问题吗?
Is there a problem here?

37
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,720
没有 名单上没有我的名字
No problem, our name's not on the list. My name's not on the list.

38
00:07:01,730 --> 00:07:05,030
那请你马上离开 没有第二条路
Then you have to leave immediately. No two ways about it.

39
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:06,760
想跳舞吗?
You want to dance?

40
00:07:06,770 --> 00:07:09,900
乔 这是阿森 没关系 他们是客人
Joe, it's Vinnie. It's okay. These are our guests.

41
00:07:09,910 --> 00:07:12,000
- 对不起 大卫 - 没关系
- I'm sorry, Dave. - It's all right.

42
00:07:12,010 --> 00:07:14,330
阿森 欢迎光临!
Vinnie, welcome to the party.

43
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:09,190
见到你真高兴
Good to see you.

44
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:11,330
我也是 这是我丈夫
It's good to see you again. This is my husband.

45
00:08:11,340 --> 00:08:14,130
这是我儿子安东尼!
This is my son, Anthony.

46
00:08:15,010 --> 00:08:19,300
圣萨巴辛勳章在教廷
The order of Saint Sebastian is one of the highest honors

47
00:08:19,310 --> 00:08:20,570
是颁给凡人的最高荣誉
the Catholic Church can bestow upon a layman.

48
00:08:20,580 --> 00:08:23,400
它始于教皇格里哥利
The award was first granted by Pope Gregory

49
00:08:23,410 --> 00:08:26,340
柯里昂先生与赌场的关系怎么办?
What about Mr. Corleone's connections with Las Vegas gambling?

50
00:08:26,450 --> 00:08:28,710
报道中有些照片...
Presskits have pictures of...

51
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,680
还有他和黑道的牵扯呢?
What about his involvement with the underworld?

52
00:08:30,690 --> 00:08:32,620
你少说废话
Cut the crap, huh?

53
00:08:32,860 --> 00:08:35,610
教皇今天亲自
The pope, the Holy Father himself

54
00:08:35,620 --> 00:08:38,550
赐福麦克柯里昂
has this very day blessed Michael Corleone.

55
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:40,830
难道你比教皇更懂?
You think you know better than the pope?

56
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:43,090
- 文森! - 干嘛?
- Vincent! - Yes?

57
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:45,890
她爱你
She loves you.

58
00:08:49,910 --> 00:08:52,270
所以? 我也爱你
Yeah? I love you, too!

59
00:08:57,680 --> 00:09:01,470
文森 我记得你
Hi Vincent. I remember you.

60
00:09:02,420 --> 00:09:04,480
记得我?在哪儿?
You remember me? From where?

61
00:09:04,490 --> 00:09:06,680
上次我们一起参加的派对
From the last time when we were at a party together

62
00:09:06,690 --> 00:09:08,220
你以前去过俱乐部?
Did you come down to the club?

63
00:09:08,230 --> 00:09:09,920
不是 是个婚礼
No, it was a wedding.

64
00:09:09,930 --> 00:09:11,590
婚礼?
A wedding?

65
00:09:12,060 --> 00:09:15,490
我八岁 你十五岁时
I was 8; and you were 15

66
00:09:15,670 --> 00:09:18,760
十五岁时我女友一大票
Well I, I had a lot of girlfriends when I was 15.

67
00:09:18,770 --> 00:09:19,830
八岁的女友?
8 year olds?

68
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:21,600
尤其是八岁
Especially 8 year olds!

69
00:09:23,210 --> 00:09:25,200
玛莉呢?
Where's Mary?

70
00:09:25,540 --> 00:09:30,280
哪位叫玛莉一声? 不好意思 阁下
Would somebody please hail Mary. Excuse me your Excellency.

71
00:09:30,580 --> 00:09:35,240
你还没给我问候吻呢 亲戚相见要相吻
You know? You haven't kissed me hello yet. Relatives always kiss.

72
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:36,640
我们是亲戚吗?
Oh, now we're related?

73
00:09:36,650 --> 00:09:38,620
我是你的小堂妹
I'm your little cousin.

74
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:47,890
你父亲是谁?
Who's your father?

75
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:52,390
给你个提示 他是意大利人
I'll give you a hint: he's Italian.

76
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:53,660
玛莉!
Mary!

77
00:09:53,670 --> 00:09:55,960
玛莉 大家都在等你呢
Mary, we've been waiting for you.

78
00:09:55,970 --> 00:10:00,200
记住声音要低 嗯?
Remember, remember now, keep your voice low, right?

79
00:10:00,210 --> 00:10:03,500
还有笑容 别忘了笑
And smile! Don't forget to smile.

80
00:10:20,970 --> 00:10:27,290
柯氏基金会荣誉主席
The honorary chairman of the Vito Corleone Foundation

81
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:30,040
小女玛莉柯里昂
My daughter, Mary Corleone.

82
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:46,150
谢谢 我大概继承了我父亲爱演说的习惯
Thanks; I think I inherited my father's love for speech making

83
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:47,890
今天是这样的
But here it goes

84
00:10:48,790 --> 00:10:53,520
柯氏基金会在世界各国济贫
The Vito Corleone Foundation helps the impoverished of every country

85
00:10:53,530 --> 00:10:57,890
资助艺术发展医学研究
gives grants to artists, funds medical research

86
00:10:57,900 --> 00:11:02,970
尤其是致力于建设西西里岛
and is particularly dedicated to the resurrection of Sicily.

87
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:05,330
基尔戴大主教
Archbishop Gilday

88
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:08,470
这是一亿美元
here is, $100,000,000

89
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:10,070
代表维多柯里昂
for the poor of Sicily

90
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:12,010
献给西西里贫民
in the name of Vito Corleone.

91
00:11:12,450 --> 00:11:14,720
不要只花在一处上!
Don't spend it all in one place!

92
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:38,770
玛莉 我真为你骄傲
Mary, I'm so proud of you.

93
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,440
麦克
Michael

94
00:11:46,850 --> 00:11:49,710
你为西西里做出了伟大的贡献
you've done a wonderful thing for Sicily.

95
00:11:50,450 --> 00:11:54,320
但愿钱用在有需要的人身上
Well, let's just hope the money gets to the people who need it.

96
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:55,780
阿们!
Amen!

97
00:11:55,790 --> 00:11:58,060
今天的重头戏
But the most important part

98
00:11:58,560 --> 00:12:01,260
强尼方亭!
Johnny Fontane!

99
00:12:09,340 --> 00:12:11,200
谢谢!
Thank you very much.

100
00:12:11,210 --> 00:12:14,070
今天来这里我很高兴
I'm happy to be here with you.

101
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:18,910
让我们同庆麦克柯里昂受封
I'd like you to join me in honoring Commendatore Michael Corleone.

102
00:12:22,550 --> 00:12:25,980
我还特别为我们的主人 我们的教父准备了礼物
And I have something special for our host and Godfather.

103
00:12:25,990 --> 00:12:28,480
我要为他演唱他最喜爱的歌
I just happen to know his favorite song.

104
00:12:28,490 --> 00:12:29,580
麦克 你上哪儿去?
Michael, where you going?

105
00:12:29,590 --> 00:12:31,050
这是你最喜欢的歌
It's your favorite song!

106
00:12:31,060 --> 00:12:34,350
我想去厨房听汤尼班的唱片
Uh, I'm off here to the kitchen to hear some Tony Bennett records.

107
00:12:35,630 --> 00:12:38,230
是你最喜欢的歌 "沙西亚所有"
It's your favorite song "Sausage" His Own.

108
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:41,330
是啊我正要去吃沙西亚三明治 一会儿就回来
That's right; a sausage sandwich! I'll be back.

109
00:13:15,870 --> 00:13:17,370
你好啊凯
Hello Kay

110
00:13:27,680 --> 00:13:31,250
恭喜了 麦克 这真是一个很大的荣耀
Well congratulations, Michael, that's really quite an honor.

111
00:13:31,260 --> 00:13:33,990
就是贵了一点 是不是?
It's a little expensive, wouldn't you say?

112
00:13:36,660 --> 00:13:38,260
蛋糕?
Cake?

113
00:13:38,530 --> 00:13:40,390
不吃 谢谢
No thank you

114
00:13:54,140 --> 00:13:56,870
- 久违了吧? - 嗯
- It's been a long time, hasn't it? - Uh huh. Yeah.

115
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:59,410
- 八年了 - 是啊
- Eight years. - Yeah.

116
00:13:59,550 --> 00:14:02,050
你看上去 很不错
You look, wonderful.

117
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:07,550
儿子有事要告诉你
Your son has something he wants to talk to you about.

118
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:09,550
我是为他事来的
I came here for him.

119
00:14:44,560 --> 00:14:45,650
当律师到底有什么不好?
What's wrong with being a lawyer?

120
00:14:45,660 --> 00:14:47,550
没有 只是他不喜欢!
Nothing, except he doesn't want it.

121
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:51,100
他热爱音乐 想投身音乐
He loves music, he wants his life to be in music.

122
00:14:51,740 --> 00:14:53,930
音乐很好 我也爱音乐
Well music is great. I love music.

123
00:14:53,940 --> 00:14:56,130
但是他做事应该有始有终
But he should finish what he started.

124
00:14:56,140 --> 00:14:57,910
安东尼...
Anthony...

125
00:14:58,040 --> 00:14:59,630
我要走自己的路
I'm going my own way.

126
00:14:59,640 --> 00:15:01,310
你的路
Your own way?

127
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:03,080
- 唱歌为业? - 是的
- Professional singer? - That's right.

128
00:15:03,550 --> 00:15:06,640
那万一…万一失败了呢?
And what happens what happens if you fail?

129
00:15:06,650 --> 00:15:08,540
我不会失败的
I won't fail.

130
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:10,080
人总是自以为是
Men always believe that.

131
00:15:10,090 --> 00:15:11,140
我知道
I know.

132
00:15:11,150 --> 00:15:14,980
如果你有个法律学位 你的人生就等于上了双保险
If you have a Law degree, you're taking out insurance.

133
00:15:14,990 --> 00:15:16,480
到时候你可以随心所欲
After that you can do whatever you want.

134
00:15:16,490 --> 00:15:19,390
- 你可以为我做事... - 我决不会为你做事
- You can work for me... - I will never work for you.

135
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:22,370
我已经有很多不好的回忆了
I have bad memories.

136
00:15:23,700 --> 00:15:27,560
每个家庭都会有些不愉快的回忆
Every family has bad memories.

137
00:15:30,140 --> 00:15:32,300
我永远是你的儿子
I will always be your son.

138
00:15:32,310 --> 00:15:35,810
但是绝不会沾手你的事业
But I will never have anything to do with your business.

139
00:15:37,150 --> 00:15:41,680
安东尼 完成法律学位课程
Anthony, finish the Law degree.

140
00:15:42,150 --> 00:15:43,890
不要!
No.

141
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:06,300
这句"不要"可是得自于你
Well, that he got from you. That "no."

142
00:16:07,640 --> 00:16:11,180
凯 你刚才应该帮我说服他
You could have helped me to convince him, Kay.

143
00:16:11,210 --> 00:16:13,640
是吗? 说服他干什么?
Oh, convince him of what?

144
00:16:13,650 --> 00:16:15,180
干什么?
Of what?

145
00:16:15,590 --> 00:16:18,480
他糟蹋了自己的人生
He throws his life away.

146
00:16:18,490 --> 00:16:21,310
他抛弃了自己将有的伟业
He throws greatness away.

147
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:23,520
这叫做伟业?
This is greatness?

148
00:16:24,490 --> 00:16:26,110
麦克 你知道吗 你现在那么受人尊敬
You know Michael, now that you're so respectable

149
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:27,920
我反而觉得你更加可怕
I think you're more dangerous than you ever were.

150
00:16:27,930 --> 00:16:34,390
其实我反而更喜欢还是普通帮派分子时的你
In fact, I preferred you when you were just a common Mafia hood.

151
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:39,500
- 好了 讲讲道理好不好? - 好
- Kay, now can we talk common sense here? - All right.

152
00:16:39,510 --> 00:16:40,940
好
Okay.

153
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:49,850
安东尼知道是你杀了弗雷多
Tony knows that you killed Fredo.

154
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:57,780
你来这里到底是为了什么?
What did you come here for?

155
00:16:57,790 --> 00:16:59,920
来保护我儿子
I came here to protect my son.

156
00:16:59,930 --> 00:17:02,590
我不是来看教廷褒扬你
I didn't come here to see you disguised by your church.

157
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:05,830
在我看来这场典礼很可耻
I think that was a shameful ceremony.

158
00:17:09,270 --> 00:17:12,400
我一辈子都在保护我的儿子
I spent my life protecting my son.

159
00:17:12,410 --> 00:17:16,240
在保护我的家庭!
I spent my life protecting my FAMILY!

160
00:17:16,250 --> 00:17:18,740
你讲讲道理好吗?
Let's be reasonable, Okay?

161
00:17:19,350 --> 00:17:22,940
你不是最讲道理的吗?
That's your big thing, isn't it, Michael?

162
00:17:22,950 --> 00:17:27,950
用杀人 来建立的道理
Reason. Backed up by murder.

163
00:17:30,260 --> 00:17:32,920
天啊你恨我 你恨我
Oh God, You hate me, you hate me.

164
00:17:32,930 --> 00:17:36,030
不
No

165
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:39,900
我不恨你
I don't hate you.

166
00:17:42,810 --> 00:17:44,130
我怕你
I dread you.

167
00:17:44,140 --> 00:17:47,700
凯 我尽我所能来保护你们
I did what I could,  Kay, to protect all of you

168
00:17:47,710 --> 00:17:50,400
不受世上的恐怖威胁
from the horrors of this world.

169
00:17:50,410 --> 00:17:53,510
你却成为了我的恐惧
But you became my horror.

170
00:18:02,390 --> 00:18:06,990
可子孩子们依然爱你 尤其是玛莉
The children still love you though. Especially Mary.

171
00:18:08,700 --> 00:18:15,530
这一点很重要 我们可以从这一点上下手
That's something. We can build on that

172
00:18:15,540 --> 00:18:17,640
为了他们
For their sake.

173
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:22,440
我们试试吧
Let's try.

174
00:18:22,450 --> 00:18:26,510
除非你让安东尼走自己的路
Only if you let Tony go free to have his own life.

175
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:28,920
远离你
Away from you.

176
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:37,550
我让安东尼走
I'll let Tony go.

177
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:41,490
谢谢你!
Thank you.

178
00:19:19,670 --> 00:19:22,700
你那鞋都能用来做武器了
You could hurt somebody with those.

179
00:19:22,970 --> 00:19:25,100
你也辛苦了大半天 我带你四处看看吧
You've been working too hard, let me show you around.

180
00:19:25,110 --> 00:19:27,630
你能不能帮我安排采访麦克柯里昂?
Can you get me an interview with Michael Corleone?

181
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:30,410
不行 虽然我是他的亲属也帮不上忙
Uh, no. I'm a relative but I can't do that.

182
00:19:30,445 --> 00:19:32,880
还有其他可以为你效劳的吗?
What else can I do for you?

183
00:19:33,420 --> 00:19:35,040
绣花枕头一个
Handsome but useless.

184
00:19:35,050 --> 00:19:36,440
是吗?
Oh yeah?

185
00:19:36,450 --> 00:19:37,810
不要紧 我愿意赌一赌
That's okay. I'll gamble.

186
00:19:37,820 --> 00:19:40,810
喜欢赌? 那我们去亚特兰大城吧
You like to gamble? Why don't we go to Atlantic City

187
00:19:40,820 --> 00:19:43,320
那是我的地盘 我来带你见识见识怎么赌一把
My town. I'll show you how to gamble.

188
00:19:43,330 --> 00:19:46,150
好啊不过我只喜欢赢 你怎么知道哪一把能赢?
Yeah, but I like to win. How will I know what numbers to pick?

189
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:48,260
你看我像个输家吗?
Do I look okay like a guy who's gonna lose?

190
00:19:48,270 --> 00:19:54,860
那个人一脸凶相吓人
Spooky looking guy there.

191
00:19:54,870 --> 00:19:58,000
这种凶煞来柯家干什么?
What is a guy like that doing at Michael Corleone's house?

192
00:19:58,010 --> 00:19:59,570
那是乔札萨的狗腿子
That's Joey Zasa's bulldog.

193
00:19:59,580 --> 00:20:00,630
你认得他?
You know that guy?

194
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:02,410
是 我认得
Yeah I know that guy.

195
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:05,640
他叫安东尼史基拉罗
That guy's name is Anthony Squigliaro.

196
00:20:05,650 --> 00:20:07,580
浑号"蚂蚁"
They call him The Ant.

197
00:20:07,750 --> 00:20:10,750
他的子弹上都涂有氰化毒
He dips his bullets in Cyanide.

198
00:20:19,060 --> 00:20:21,160
艾图贝洛阁下
Don Altobello

199
00:20:22,270 --> 00:20:24,890
我来表示敬意
I came to pay my respects

200
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:26,670
谢谢
Grazie.

201
00:20:29,070 --> 00:20:31,670
你是我父亲的挚友
You honor my father's friendship.

202
00:20:31,940 --> 00:20:34,640
我的教女在哪里?
Where is my goddaughter?

203
00:20:38,650 --> 00:20:43,850
想当年你还不过是我手里抱着的小娃娃
It was not so long ago I held you in these old hands

204
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:47,010
麦克
Michael

205
00:20:47,020 --> 00:20:48,450
请坐!
Piachere? Cominar

206
00:20:48,460 --> 00:20:51,350
站着可以了
No, I stand; I stand

207
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:56,760
麦克 我已经老了 不再有年轻人的活力和愤怒了
Michael, I lost all the venom, all the juice of youth.

208
00:20:56,770 --> 00:20:59,890
对女人也失去了欲望
I lost the lust for women

209
00:20:59,900 --> 00:21:02,530
现在我的头脑很清楚
and now my mind is clear

210
00:21:02,540 --> 00:21:05,600
知道自己对上主的职责
My duty to God is clear

211
00:21:05,610 --> 00:21:10,010
有件特别的事我想要你帮忙
I have a special favor to ask

212
00:21:10,380 --> 00:21:18,040
能不能让我加入柯氏基金会
Can I attach my name to the Vito Corleone Foundation

213
00:21:18,050 --> 00:21:24,490
以使你我能更全面地融合一体
so that you and I can be joined in name and spirit

214
00:21:25,630 --> 00:21:27,950
一百万美金
One million dollars

215
00:21:33,340 --> 00:21:34,590
教父
Godfather

216
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:37,770
你真善心
Don Altobello, you have such heart

217
00:21:40,380 --> 00:21:45,480
走 我们去喝杯酒
Come; let's go and sample some of Italy vino.

218
00:21:51,450 --> 00:21:54,950
梵蒂冈教廷对这些股东的背景全然不知
The Vatican knows nothing about these shareholders

219
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:56,220
好!
Good

220
00:21:56,230 --> 00:21:58,420
我一向杞人忧天
I have a tendency to worry

221
00:21:58,430 --> 00:22:02,360
我担心太明显 会让人起疑
We've increased our position substantially and naturally I worry

222
00:22:02,370 --> 00:22:06,730
别担心! 我们签有合约
Stop worrying. We have an agreement.

223
00:22:06,740 --> 00:22:09,760
那就好 我担心得头发也白了
Good. How do you think I got this grey hair?

224
00:22:09,770 --> 00:22:13,270
- 柯里昂先生 耽误…两秒钟 - 法兰克 你好吗?
- Mr. Corleone, two seconds - Frank, how are you?

225
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:15,770
谢谢你对游泳池建设的贡献
Thank you very much for your contribution to the Board's swimming pool.

226
00:22:15,780 --> 00:22:20,070
另外我们希望你能支持华里士竞选法官
And we need your help on Sam Wallace's candidacy for judgeship.

227
00:22:20,080 --> 00:22:22,610
- 一个好法官总是有用的 - 谢谢你
- We always can use a good judge. - Thank you

228
00:22:22,620 --> 00:22:24,280
安德鲁!
Andrew!

229
00:22:24,490 --> 00:22:26,490
阁下 我的教子安德鲁哈金
Your Excellency, my Godson, Andrew Hagan,

230
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:28,680
我的兄弟汤姆的大儿子
my brother Tom Hagan's eldest boy.

231
00:22:28,690 --> 00:22:33,050
他在毕兰主教座下已有多年
He's been assistant to Bishop Greening for years now.

232
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:34,960
期望调任梵蒂冈
Hoping for an assignment to the Vatican.

233
00:22:34,970 --> 00:22:37,490
年轻优秀的教士罗马随时欢迎
There's always a place in Rome for a fine young priest.

234
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:41,200
他的母亲 泰瑞莎 这是基尔戴大主教
His mother Theresa Hagen Archbishop Gilday

235
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,200
幸会
Honored to meet you.

236
00:22:43,210 --> 00:22:46,240
柯先生 你好 我是葛莉丝汉摩顿
Mr. Corleone. Hi, Grace Hamilton.

237
00:22:47,210 --> 00:22:49,940
文森曼西尼对我说会向你提起我
Vincent Mancini promised that he'd tell you about me.

238
00:22:49,950 --> 00:22:51,680
说也许你会见我
that maybe you'd see me.

239
00:22:52,180 --> 00:22:55,680
- 文森曼西尼可有提到她? - 没有
- Vincent Mancini called about her? - No

240
00:22:55,690 --> 00:22:57,910
葛莉丝你答应我不乱跑的
Grace, you promised me you'd stay up there.

241
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:59,120
- 我知道! - 两次了!
- I know. - Twice.

242
00:23:00,860 --> 00:23:02,950
札萨来了
Joey Zasa showed up.

243
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:04,780
我让他在外厅等
We've got him waiting in the lobby.

244
00:23:04,790 --> 00:23:09,260
他说要亲自向你道贺…致敬
Says he wants to personally congratulate you and show his respect.

245
00:23:09,270 --> 00:23:10,990
我非得见他?
Do I have to see him?

246
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:12,730
他说你是他的老大
He says you're his patrone.

247
00:23:12,740 --> 00:23:14,970
而且只要求一分钟
and he only wants a minute.

248
00:23:17,640 --> 00:23:21,530
文森 你最喜欢哪个姑姑?
Hey Vinnie! Who's your favorite Aunt?

249
00:23:21,540 --> 00:23:23,040
你!
You are.

250
00:23:26,020 --> 00:23:29,220
今天我会跟麦克提你的事情
Today I'm gonna talk to Michael about your little problem.

251
00:23:30,190 --> 00:23:32,010
你该早告诉我
I wish you would have warned me Conn',

252
00:23:32,020 --> 00:23:34,150
我也好穿得光鲜一点
I could have worn a better suit.

253
00:23:35,090 --> 00:23:38,080
米乌奇协会选你
The Meucci Association has elected you,

254
00:23:38,090 --> 00:23:41,390
为今年度意裔楷模
their Italian-American Man of the Year.

255
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:44,490
米乌奇
Meucci

256
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:48,630
米乌奇是谁?
Who's Meucci?

257
00:23:49,510 --> 00:23:52,070
意裔美籍他发明电话
He's the Italian-American who invented the telephone.

258
00:23:52,080 --> 00:23:55,870
比贝尔早了一年
He did it one year before Alexander Graham Bell.

259
00:23:59,580 --> 00:24:03,610
挑今天来只为这档子事?
And this is the reason you've come to my home on this day.

260
00:24:04,890 --> 00:24:07,120
去把鱼喂了
Go feed the fish.

261
00:24:09,790 --> 00:24:17,920
有件事情让我很不痛快
I got a stone in my shoe, Mr. Corleone.

262
00:24:17,930 --> 00:24:21,190
有个替我跑腿的小瘪三
A two-bit punk who works for me

263
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:26,100
他自命是你的亲属
The one who, thinks he's related to you.

264
00:24:26,980 --> 00:24:29,510
小混蛋!
A bastard.

265
00:24:32,420 --> 00:24:33,770
他在这里
He's here.

266
00:24:33,780 --> 00:24:38,020
文森曼西尼 他在宴会上!
Vincent Mancini. He's at the party.

267
00:24:40,120 --> 00:24:42,250
带他进来!
Well bring him in.

268
00:24:43,130 --> 00:24:46,490
我们谈就好了
I think it's good we talk.

269
00:24:46,500 --> 00:24:49,290
不用 谢谢!
No thanks.

270
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:52,470
我有个有麻烦
I have a problem

271
00:24:52,770 --> 00:24:57,560
我要弄清楚这到底是我的
and I want to find out if it is my problem

272
00:24:57,670 --> 00:24:59,270
还是你的麻烦
or your problem

273
00:24:59,280 --> 00:25:01,130
乔 你做你的买卖
Joe, your business is your business.

274
00:25:01,140 --> 00:25:03,740
我不沾利益也不分红
I have no interests or percentage.

275
00:25:03,750 --> 00:25:05,380
我是局外人
I'm out

276
00:25:05,580 --> 00:25:07,210
很好!
Good.

277
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:09,780
那么就是我的麻烦了
Then it's my problem.

278
00:25:13,120 --> 00:25:16,520
麦克 你认得文森
Michael, you know Vincent Mancini

279
00:25:16,530 --> 00:25:18,290
大哥的遗孤
Sonny's boy.

280
00:25:19,660 --> 00:25:21,690
柯里昂先生 你好吗?
How you doin' Mr. Corleone?

281
00:25:21,760 --> 00:25:22,860
你好吗?
How you doing?

282
00:25:22,870 --> 00:25:24,120
很好 你好吗?
I'm doin' good. How you doin'?

283
00:25:24,130 --> 00:25:25,890
- 很好! - 好一场盛宴
- Good. - Good party.

284
00:25:25,900 --> 00:25:26,960
你喜欢?
Oh you like it?

285
00:25:26,970 --> 00:25:28,460
是 我溜进来的
Yeah, I had to sneak in.

286
00:25:28,470 --> 00:25:30,240
至少你盛装前来
Well, you're dressed for it.

287
00:25:34,580 --> 00:25:39,680
你和札萨先生有什么过节吗?
So, what's the trouble between you and Mr. Joe Zasa?

288
00:25:40,850 --> 00:25:43,240
小麻烦 我会摆平
There's trouble. I'll take care of it.

289
00:25:44,020 --> 00:25:45,350
你这样非常愚蠢
That's foolish of you.

290
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:47,110
我愚蠢?
Foolish of ME?

291
00:25:47,120 --> 00:25:49,450
这家伙才愚蠢
It's a little foolish of this guy

292
00:25:49,460 --> 00:25:51,190
对不对?
Don't you think?

293
00:25:51,900 --> 00:25:53,920
对不对? 对不对?
Right? RIGHT?

294
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,860
脾气火爆还真像他爸
Temper like his father.

295
00:25:55,870 --> 00:26:01,190
文森 目前札萨先生拥有…
Vincent. Mr. Joe Zasa now owns

296
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:04,760
昔日柯里昂家在纽约的生意
what used to be the Corleone family business, in New York.

297
00:26:04,770 --> 00:26:08,770
他好意把你安插在他帮中
Out of the kindness of his heart he gave you a job in his family.

298
00:26:08,780 --> 00:26:11,700
你不听我劝硬要接受
Contrary to my advice, you took the job.

299
00:26:11,710 --> 00:26:15,380
我给你提供一了个更好的合法工作
I'd offered you something, better, in the legitimate world.

300
00:26:15,390 --> 00:26:16,940
你回绝了
You turned me down.

301
00:26:16,950 --> 00:26:20,980
现在你们结了怨便来找我
Now, you both come to me with this bad blood.

302
00:26:20,990 --> 00:26:23,160
你还指望我怎么做?
And what do you expect me to do?

303
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:25,220
难道我是个流氓头吗?
Am I a gangster?

304
00:26:25,230 --> 00:26:26,320
不是!你不是流氓头
No, you're not a gangster.

305
00:26:26,330 --> 00:26:27,990
爸爸的以前的老邻里都被搞得乌烟瘴气
That's was Papa's neighborhood, now it's a sewer.

306
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:30,190
札萨根本没有用心在打理
Zasa runs it like a disgrace that's what the women tell me.

307
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:32,130
康妮 那是旧事
That's the past Connie.

308
00:26:32,140 --> 00:26:34,860
我靠自己的本事赚得那块地盘
I earned that territory with my talent.

309
00:26:34,870 --> 00:26:38,700
帮会分配给我 你也同意
Commission gave it to me, and you approved.

310
00:26:38,710 --> 00:26:39,870
是的!
Yes.

311
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:41,130
麦克叔
Uncle Michael

312
00:26:41,140 --> 00:26:42,770
我来赴宴不是求援
I came to the party here I'm not here to ask for any kind of help

313
00:26:42,780 --> 00:26:43,940
我完全杀的了这混帐
I could just kill this bastard

314
00:26:43,950 --> 00:26:45,000
需要帮助的是他
He's the one who needs the help.

315
00:26:45,010 --> 00:26:46,910
那杀了他啊
So kill him

316
00:26:47,650 --> 00:26:50,810
你们的事和我有什么关系?
What has all this have to do with me?

317
00:26:50,820 --> 00:26:52,020
背着你他经常骂
Well, he's going around behind your back saying

318
00:26:52,030 --> 00:26:53,510
"去他妈的麦克柯里昂"
fuck Michael Corleone all time.

319
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:56,150
这跟你相干了吧
That's it, see, that's one thing it has to do with you

320
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:59,950
当他的面骂一次 当他的面骂一次啊！
Say it to his face, one time. Say it to his face, one time!

321
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:03,420
柯里昂先生 混蛋都撒谎
Mr. Corleone, all bastards are liars.

322
00:27:03,430 --> 00:27:05,290
莎士比亚的诗句中都这么写
Shakespeare wrote poems about it.

323
00:27:05,300 --> 00:27:06,660
麦克叔 我该怎么处置他?
What am I gonna do with this guy, Uncle Michael?

324
00:27:06,670 --> 00:27:08,700
怎么处置他?
WHAT AM I GONNA DO WITH THIS GUY?

325
00:27:14,710 --> 00:27:16,640
乔
Joey

326
00:27:16,650 --> 00:27:19,810
如有人在市里到处跑
If there's some guy running around this city

327
00:27:19,820 --> 00:27:23,050
还骂"妈的麦克柯里昂"
saying "fuck Michael Corleone"

328
00:27:23,690 --> 00:27:28,420
这种杂碎我们怎么处置?
what do we do, with a piece of shit like that?

329
00:27:29,290 --> 00:27:32,030
把他当狗东西 不是吗?
He's a fucking dog. No?

330
00:27:38,300 --> 00:27:41,820
对! 说这种话的人
Yes it's true. If anyone would say such a thing,

331
00:27:41,830 --> 00:27:43,530
肯定不是朋友
they would not be a friend.

332
00:27:43,540 --> 00:27:45,700
就是个狗东西
They would be a dog.

333
00:27:51,610 --> 00:27:54,070
我同札萨先生没有利害冲突
My interests don't conflict with Mr. Joe Zasa's

334
00:27:54,080 --> 00:27:54,800
你只是还不知道
Oh you don't know how much

335
00:27:54,810 --> 00:27:57,840
你跟他大有冲突
your interests conflict with Mr. Joe Zasa's, Uncle Michael.

336
00:27:57,850 --> 00:27:59,450
文森
Vinnie

337
00:27:59,460 --> 00:28:01,880
麦克 支持他
He needs your support, Michael.

338
00:28:01,890 --> 00:28:03,180
别让我再做他手下了
Don't let me word for this guy no more Uncle Michael.

339
00:28:03,190 --> 00:28:04,620
让我来帮你
let me come work for you.

340
00:28:04,630 --> 00:28:05,720
- 替我做事? - 是的
- For me? - Yeah.

341
00:28:05,730 --> 00:28:07,450
做什么? 当打手?
As what? Tough guy?

342
00:28:07,460 --> 00:28:11,890
我用不着打手 律师倒多多益善
I don't need tough guys. I need more lawyers.

343
00:28:13,940 --> 00:28:16,760
既然无怨无债
Since we have no conflicts, no debts

344
00:28:16,770 --> 00:28:21,900
我接受馈赠并祝你如意
I accept your tribute. I wish you well.

345
00:28:21,910 --> 00:28:26,770
文森 同札萨先生和好 来!
Vincent, Make your peace with Mr. Joe Zasa. C'mon

346
00:28:29,820 --> 00:28:31,480
好 去啊
Okay. Go on.

347
00:28:37,390 --> 00:28:39,890
小混蛋
Bastardo.

348
00:28:43,630 --> 00:28:45,290
文森
Vincent

349
00:28:45,300 --> 00:28:47,570
天啊! 快停下来 你疯了?
For Christ's sakes, stop! What's the matter with you?

350
00:28:47,640 --> 00:28:49,400
把他弄走!
Get him out of here.

351
00:28:50,970 --> 00:28:53,400
我的天!
Oh,Jesus.

352
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:56,440
麦克叔 我跟姑姑说过现在还不是时候
Uncle Michael, I told Connie it wasn't the right time for this.

353
00:28:56,450 --> 00:28:57,970
关门
Close it.

354
00:28:57,980 --> 00:28:59,340
我知道你现在转入金融证券界
I know you're into banks and Wall Street

355
00:28:59,350 --> 00:29:01,740
但帮里事务仍由你作主
But everyone knows you're the final word, like the Supreme Court.

356
00:29:01,750 --> 00:29:04,710
我要保护你 你的律师办不到
I want to protect you from these guys. Your lawyers can't do that.

357
00:29:04,720 --> 00:29:07,320
- 你办得到? - 是 我办得到
- And you can? - Yeah, I can do that.

358
00:29:09,030 --> 00:29:11,220
我何必怕札萨?
And why should I be afraid of Joe Zasa?

359
00:29:11,230 --> 00:29:12,280
他知道你妨碍他
Well, he knows you're stopping him

